   CCR Newsletter

   The next issue of the CCR's scientific newsletter, Frontiers in
   Science, will be published this fall and features a message from Dr.
   Barrett as well as a new feature highlighting the Center's current
   clinical trials. Scientific topics will encompass:
     * Improving cancer immunotherapy/Drs. Masaki Terabe and Jay Berzofsky
     * Strategies to enhance the potency of cancer vaccines/Drs. James
       Hodge and Jeffrey Schlom
     * Ligand interactions at the diacylglycerol receptors: Emerging
       insights/Dr. Peter Blumberg
     * Single-molecule biology: New insights into macromolecule
       behavior/Dr. Sanford Leuba
     * Proteolysis: Molecular architecture of the ATP-dependent
       proteases/Dr. Michael Maurizi
     * Structure-based drug design: Identifying new, unique
       antibiotics/Dr. Xinhua Ji

   The most recent newsletters for the former Division of Basic Sciences
   (DBS) and the Division of Clinical Sciences (DCS) are available below
   in PDF format.
